OpenAMRobot Platform Hardware

This repository is part of the OpenAMRobot open-source robotics ecosystem
(https://github.com/openAMRobot, https://botshare.ai). It contains the
hardware documentation for the OpenAMRobot mobile base: electrical wiring
and pinouts, power distribution, sensor and motor-control notes, the bill of
materials, and safety documentation.

Per-asset licensing:
- Documentation, notes, and BOM (all Markdown/text currently in this repo):
  MIT (the license above), Copyright (c) 2026 OpenAMRobot.
- Software-related scripts (if/when added): MIT.
- Hardware design files (CAD, schematics, PCB layouts) — the mechanical/,
  CAD, and PCB directories are currently EMPTY PLACEHOLDERS. When such design
  files are added, they will be licensed under CERN-OHL-S-2.0, and this file
  will be updated to carve them out explicitly.

Important notice:
This documentation describes a physical robot with motors and batteries. Users
are responsible for validating wiring, power, mechanical, and electrical safety
before building or operating hardware based on it. Provided for educational,
research, and development purposes.

